<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17869] TopGroupsShardRequestFactory creates sub-requests with timeAllowed=1 when limit has already expired</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17869</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TopGroupsShardRequestFactory&lt;/tt&gt; has code that looks like this...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; origTimeAllowed = sreq.params.getInt(CommonParams.TIME_ALLOWED, -1);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (origTimeAllowed &amp;gt; 0) {
      sreq.params.set(
          CommonParams.TIME_ALLOWED, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.max(1, origTimeAllowed - rb.firstPhaseElapsedTime));
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this code, the use of &lt;tt&gt;Math.max()&lt;/tt&gt; means that even if the time limit has already expired, Solr will still create &amp;amp; send a sub-shard request with a &lt;tt&gt;timeAllowed=1&lt;/tt&gt; param.  Solr should not be sending the sub-request at all in this situation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
